<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-09-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-09-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 21158/4.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Kerens</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-09-22"><hi rend="italic">September 22,
                                    1910</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 105.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my dispatch No. 66 of July
                            30, 1910, transmitting the sworn statement and passport application of
                            Mr. Rudolf Warren-Lippit, may I inquire if the department has reached a
                            decision in the matter, and, if so, the result of same?</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. C. Kerens.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>